<br>
I did think about using the kyu/dan terminology for Bjond (he's a monk), but I didn't think anyone would get it if I said I was 28th kyu, which would mean 22nd level.  Kyu counts down to 1, which is just before the 1st dan rank, which then count back up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utitaisia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Titaisia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/16/02 10:00:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1107.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie tips (seem to be quite a few new players lately)</span><hr size=1> Use level if you feel comfortable with it.  People will figure out what you mean probably no matter what you use.  It just isn't for me! <p>Titaisia<BR>
